1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:00,900
<i> Aah!</i>

2
00:00:01,067 --> 00:00:02,567
[MOTORCYCLE HONKING]

3
00:00:02,700 --> 00:00:04,733
[SQUEALS, GRUNTS]

4
00:00:04,867 --> 00:00:05,867
<i> Why do you have this?</i>

5
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:07,667
<i>- I saw it--
- This is ours!</i>

6
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:12,067
<i>We should protect each other,
and that includes Mom.</i>

7
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:15,100
<i>I'm sorry if I was the reason
they fought.</i>

8
00:00:15,233 --> 00:00:16,300
<i> Does Martin know about this?</i>

9
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:18,667
<i>It's Kiko. He was the one
who found the earring.</i>

10
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,967
<i>We shouldn't let the police
know about this, okay?</i>

11
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:22,300
<i> Was this Mrs. Almazan?</i>

12
00:00:22,433 --> 00:00:24,133
<i>It was recorded
from a car's dashcam</i>

13
00:00:24,267 --> 00:00:26,967
<i>on the day Michael Fernandez
and Federico Almazan died.</i>

14
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:28,133
<i>- The earring?
- That's ours.</i>

15
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:31,567
<i>- We apologize because--
- Because I lost it.</i>

16
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:33,833
<i> The earring is mine.</i>

17
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,067
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

18
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:41,000
I misplaced it near the place
where Dad died.

19
00:00:44,033 --> 00:00:45,867
What were you doing there?

20
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,500
Am I not allowed to visit?

21
00:00:47,633 --> 00:00:50,000
Why not at the cemetery
where your dad is buried?

22
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:52,233
What do you even care?

23
00:00:52,367 --> 00:00:54,500
I wanted to go where my
Dad had last stepped in.

24
00:00:54,633 --> 00:00:57,467
Do I seriously have to ask
your permission for that, Gio?

25
00:00:58,833 --> 00:00:59,900
Gio.

26
00:01:00,033 --> 00:01:04,467
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

27
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,067
So, are we good?

28
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,933
Are things clear to you now?

29
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:15,100
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

30
00:01:15,233 --> 00:01:17,567
Or maybe you still have
something to ask?

31
00:01:20,667 --> 00:01:24,000
[LEON] I hope this will no
longer cause any issues at work.

32
00:01:24,133 --> 00:01:25,800
[MARTIN] Of course.

33
00:01:25,933 --> 00:01:27,867
Let's make it official then.

34
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,667
Welcome to Hotel 88.

35
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:36,633
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

36
00:01:41,767 --> 00:01:42,933
I'll see you around.

37
00:01:43,067 --> 00:01:48,967
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

38
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:51,267
So, the earring belongs to Luna?

39
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:53,933
Am I the only one
who doesn't believe

40
00:01:54,067 --> 00:01:55,633
what those siblings said?

41
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:58,533
They had different reactions.

42
00:01:59,367 --> 00:02:01,933
Justin acts off. He just goes
along with his sister.

43
00:02:02,067 --> 00:02:04,467
Jade looked at Luna strangely.

44
00:02:05,933 --> 00:02:07,333
What do you mean?

45
00:02:08,067 --> 00:02:10,633
I don't know.
I just can't explain it.

46
00:02:11,933 --> 00:02:13,600
All I know is that...

47
00:02:14,367 --> 00:02:16,467
they are obviously
hiding something.

48
00:02:19,033 --> 00:02:21,100
I will try to talk to Jade.

49
00:02:21,233 --> 00:02:23,333
She might be able to tell me.

50
00:02:23,467 --> 00:02:25,000
Do you think it's that easy?

51
00:02:25,133 --> 00:02:26,433
Remember, she's an Almazan.

52
00:02:26,567 --> 00:02:28,567
She'll protect her family
no matter what.

53
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:31,233
There's nothing wrong
with trying, right?

54
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:33,567
So, you guys
take care of the hotel.

55
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:36,167
I'll find out the truth
through Jade.

56
00:02:37,033 --> 00:02:38,233
Okay.

57
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:40,700
So, you're going to use Jade?

58
00:02:40,833 --> 00:02:47,700
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

59
00:02:49,367 --> 00:02:56,367
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

60
00:02:58,867 --> 00:03:04,467
[WAVES LAPPING, SPLASHING]

61
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:11,167
- [BATS SCREECHING]
- [BIRDS CHIRPING]

62
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:17,133
- [SHOVEL DIGGING]
- [OWL HOOTING]

63
00:03:17,267 --> 00:03:22,067
[SLOW HEAVY FOOTSTEPS]

64
00:03:22,233 --> 00:03:29,167
- [EERIE NOISE]
- [UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

65
00:03:30,367 --> 00:03:33,367
[GUN CLANKS]

66
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:41,300
- [BICYCLE WHEELS ROLLING]
- [GROUND SHAKING, CRUMBLING]

67
00:03:50,033 --> 00:03:52,000
I won't use her.

68
00:03:52,133 --> 00:03:54,800
Besides, we're not
that kind of people.

69
00:03:54,967 --> 00:03:56,633
Jade and I used to be close.

70
00:03:56,767 --> 00:03:58,900
We were friends
when we were kids.

71
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:03,167
I'll try to talk to her nicely.

72
00:04:03,300 --> 00:04:04,433
[MARTIN HUFFS]

73
00:04:04,567 --> 00:04:05,833
Okay.

74
00:04:05,967 --> 00:04:08,767
If you think you can convince
her to speak the truth...

75
00:04:09,633 --> 00:04:10,767
do it.

76
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:15,933
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

77
00:04:16,067 --> 00:04:17,633
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

78
00:04:19,067 --> 00:04:20,300
I have a project in mind.

79
00:04:20,433 --> 00:04:22,533
Let's see if Luna
can still say no.

80
00:04:23,333 --> 00:04:24,767
Speaking of...

81
00:04:25,767 --> 00:04:28,500
[LUNA] Everyone,
this is Edward Arellano.

82
00:04:28,667 --> 00:04:31,600
He will help us
promote Hotel 88.

83
00:04:32,267 --> 00:04:34,533
Edward, they're
Uncle Michael's children.

84
00:04:34,667 --> 00:04:36,433
They are also co-owners
of Hotel 88.

85
00:04:36,567 --> 00:04:40,067
- The Operations Manager...
- Martin Madrigal.

86
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:41,233
Of course.

87
00:04:41,367 --> 00:04:43,333
We know each other.

88
00:04:43,467 --> 00:04:44,800
[LUNA] Right.

89
00:04:44,933 --> 00:04:46,667
He also reached out to you.

90
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:51,400
- Good to see you here.
- [EDWARD] Good to see you.

91
00:04:52,033 --> 00:04:53,500
Gio...

92
00:04:53,633 --> 00:04:55,700
Gio is in charge of sales.

93
00:04:56,233 --> 00:04:57,467
Edward.

94
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,267
[GIO HUFFS]

95
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:00,900
Mm.

96
00:05:03,167 --> 00:05:06,133
Kiko is in charge
of housekeeping,

97
00:05:06,267 --> 00:05:08,367
including food and beverages.

98
00:05:13,533 --> 00:05:16,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

99
00:05:16,867 --> 00:05:17,833
It's all good.

100
00:05:17,967 --> 00:05:19,833
Welcome to Hotel 88.

101
00:05:19,967 --> 00:05:24,367
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

102
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:27,267
So, can we go back to work?

103
00:05:29,900 --> 00:05:31,067
- Jade.
- [JADE] Mm?

104
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,667
Tour me around.

105
00:05:34,433 --> 00:05:35,800
Let's go.

106
00:05:35,933 --> 00:05:40,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

107
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:42,067
[JADE] Excuse me.

108
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:49,533
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

109
00:05:52,700 --> 00:05:56,367
[SIGHS IN RELIEF] Good thing
I was able to convince Edward.

110
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:59,300
It's a great help that he's
a family friend of ours.

111
00:05:59,433 --> 00:06:00,633
[SLOW CLAPPING]

112
00:06:00,767 --> 00:06:02,033
Impressive!

113
00:06:02,167 --> 00:06:03,867
You're so great, Luna.

114
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:07,700
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

115
00:06:07,867 --> 00:06:09,267
Martin...

116
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:12,567
Next time, inform me if you have
anything to do for the hotel.

117
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:16,067
- So, none of us gets surprised.
- [MARTIN SCOFFS]

118
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:17,467
Of course.

119
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:19,567
You are the GM after all.

120
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:21,800
I really need
to keep you updated.

121
00:06:21,933 --> 00:06:23,600
[CLICKS MOUTH] Okay.

122
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:25,967
Thanks!

123
00:06:30,433 --> 00:06:31,900
[KIKO] Jade.

124
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:34,433
- Kiko.
- [KIKO] Can I talk to you?

125
00:06:34,567 --> 00:06:37,300
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

126
00:06:37,433 --> 00:06:40,033
Once... Once you're done.

127
00:06:40,167 --> 00:06:46,033
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

128
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,933
Let's go?

129
00:06:51,167 --> 00:06:55,933
[WAVES LAPPING, SPLASHING]

130
00:06:56,067 --> 00:06:58,067
Do you know that Edward?

131
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,833
Yes.

132
00:06:59,967 --> 00:07:01,700
Actually, I was the one
who thought of hiring Edward

133
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:03,767
to boost the bookings
of the hotel.

134
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:07,533
But Luna didn't tell me
that she's long known him.

135
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:10,700
[CLEARS THROAT]

136
00:07:10,833 --> 00:07:12,133
It's obvious.

137
00:07:12,267 --> 00:07:14,767
That family's seriously
playing tricks against us.

138
00:07:14,933 --> 00:07:17,733
They're even desperate
to get Edward first.

139
00:07:19,033 --> 00:07:21,367
That Luna is really
something else, huh?

140
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:24,667
Goodness,
she's always been like that.

141
00:07:25,433 --> 00:07:27,867
What do you know about Luna?

142
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:30,633
Never mind.

143
00:07:30,767 --> 00:07:33,100
D-Do you guys have a past?

144
00:07:34,367 --> 00:07:35,467
Yeah.

145
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,800
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

146
00:07:37,933 --> 00:07:39,067
What?!

147
00:07:40,367 --> 00:07:42,100
And her demeanor?

148
00:07:42,667 --> 00:07:44,867
She's not the Luna
I've known before.

149
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:49,533
Perhaps I should remind her
of who she truly is.

150
00:07:51,033 --> 00:07:53,100
W-What do you mean?

151
00:07:54,967 --> 00:07:57,400
Just think of this
as my way of helping you.

152
00:07:57,533 --> 00:07:59,500
You want to be the GM,
don't you?

153
00:07:59,633 --> 00:08:05,533
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

154
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:07,467
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

155
00:08:09,533 --> 00:08:10,900
You've seen all the rooms.

156
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:13,400
Luna said you can stay
in any of the rooms.

157
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,267
Just inform--

158
00:08:14,267 --> 00:08:16,300
I'm okay with
the executive rooms.

159
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:18,733
We just need
additional services.

160
00:08:18,733 --> 00:08:20,733
Cheaper rooms get booked fast.

161
00:08:20,733 --> 00:08:23,033
The bigger rooms are the ones
that need to be promoted.

162
00:08:23,067 --> 00:08:25,400
Okay. Copy. Noted.

163
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:28,600
The restaurant also serves
Western and local cuisines.

164
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,667
Why did you suddenly
leave me at the café?

165
00:08:30,667 --> 00:08:33,833
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

166
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:35,467
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

167
00:08:35,467 --> 00:08:39,900
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

168
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:43,567
Daily happy hour runs
from 3 to 5 p.m. for drinks.

169
00:08:43,567 --> 00:08:46,867
That's fifty percent,
so it'll help promote the hotel.

170
00:08:46,867 --> 00:08:49,900
Luna said you can also order
anything on the menu.

171
00:08:49,900 --> 00:08:51,667
On the house.

172
00:08:51,667 --> 00:08:53,033
Okay.

173
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:54,600
Copy.

174
00:08:54,633 --> 00:08:56,333
Noted.

175
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:57,667
[SIGHS]

176
00:09:00,767 --> 00:09:02,600
Jade, are you okay?

177
00:09:04,433 --> 00:09:06,467
I've covered everything,
haven't I?

178
00:09:06,467 --> 00:09:07,867
We're done.

179
00:09:07,867 --> 00:09:10,033
Jade, you're not answering
my question.

180
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:13,733
Oh, wait. Jade.

181
00:09:14,567 --> 00:09:15,700
Jade.

182
00:09:17,367 --> 00:09:18,700
Yes.

183
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:19,967
Yes, I'm okay.

184
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:24,900
Let's continue our lunch here.

185
00:09:26,767 --> 00:09:28,667
I don't have time for that.

186
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:32,033
As far as I know,
the tour ended early.

187
00:09:33,033 --> 00:09:34,867
So, you still have time.

188
00:09:35,633 --> 00:09:37,567
I'll repeat.

189
00:09:37,567 --> 00:09:39,433
Just because there's more time

190
00:09:39,433 --> 00:09:41,467
doesn't mean
it should be wasted.

191
00:09:42,033 --> 00:09:46,600
We haven't even discussed
the social media plan yet.

192
00:09:47,433 --> 00:09:49,400
You call that wasting time?

193
00:09:53,767 --> 00:09:55,600
Lunch at the restaurant?

194
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:57,133
No.

195
00:09:57,133 --> 00:09:59,367
What's wrong
with a music festival?

196
00:10:00,033 --> 00:10:03,067
Big setup, big budget,
big overhead!

197
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:05,500
The hotel has just been opened.

198
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:07,433
[LUNA] We can't handle that.

199
00:10:07,433 --> 00:10:09,467
[JUSTIN] Luna's right.
My suggestion--

200
00:10:09,467 --> 00:10:12,000
[LUNA] We're not even done
with Edward's promotion yet.

201
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,067
[MARTIN] And so?

202
00:10:13,067 --> 00:10:15,967
We're just going to rely
on one form of promotion?

203
00:10:15,967 --> 00:10:19,033
[GIO] It's not just hotel guests
bringing money in.

204
00:10:19,033 --> 00:10:20,200
When we have events like this,

205
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:23,400
we can generate income
from those checked in elsewhere.

206
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:25,133
Like a music festival!

207
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:29,167
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

208
00:10:29,167 --> 00:10:30,433
Leon.

209
00:10:30,433 --> 00:10:32,967
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

210
00:10:32,967 --> 00:10:34,400
Say something?

211
00:10:36,567 --> 00:10:38,733
[MARTIN SIGHS SHARPLY]

212
00:10:38,733 --> 00:10:40,733
Yes. It needs a lot of money,

213
00:10:40,733 --> 00:10:42,633
but the returns are high.

214
00:10:42,633 --> 00:10:45,833
Revenue, hotel promotion...

215
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:48,800
partnerships we can use
in the future.

216
00:10:50,167 --> 00:10:52,433
- Luna, can you hear them?
- I said no.

217
00:10:52,433 --> 00:10:54,667
- Let's consider it, Luna.
- Leon!

218
00:10:55,967 --> 00:10:57,767
They're right.

219
00:10:57,767 --> 00:10:59,467
Lots of returns.

220
00:11:00,033 --> 00:11:01,133
It's easier to sell tickets

221
00:11:01,133 --> 00:11:03,900
because there are more tourists
during a festival

222
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:06,033
compared to the off-season.

223
00:11:09,167 --> 00:11:11,033
I can push this event.

224
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:13,133
You?

225
00:11:13,133 --> 00:11:15,167
Can you?

226
00:11:15,167 --> 00:11:17,467
Are you kidding me?

227
00:11:17,467 --> 00:11:19,833
But if the hotel loses money,

228
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:22,000
it's your fault,
and I'll make you pay for it!

229
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,633
[CHAIR THUDS, SCRAPES]

230
00:11:23,633 --> 00:11:26,967
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

231
00:11:26,967 --> 00:11:34,133
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

232
00:11:37,233 --> 00:11:42,133
[PHONE RINGING]

233
00:11:42,167 --> 00:11:44,133
Yo, bro.

234
00:11:44,133 --> 00:11:46,267
Yeah. How are you?

235
00:11:46,267 --> 00:11:48,200
No, no, no, no.
I'm not busy.

236
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,633
No, no, no.

237
00:11:49,633 --> 00:11:50,733
What's up?

238
00:11:51,667 --> 00:11:53,633
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

239
00:11:53,633 --> 00:11:55,567
No problem, yeah. What's up?

240
00:11:55,567 --> 00:11:57,133
[SIGHS SHARPLY]

241
00:11:58,233 --> 00:11:59,633
Jade!

242
00:11:59,633 --> 00:12:00,967
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

243
00:12:00,967 --> 00:12:03,000
- Jade!
- [EDWARD SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY]

244
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:05,867
- [JADE HUFFS]
- [HEAVY FOOTSTEPS]

245
00:12:05,867 --> 00:12:07,167
Jade!

246
00:12:07,167 --> 00:12:14,133
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

247
00:12:16,233 --> 00:12:17,700
[KIKO] Jade?

248
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:26,267
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:12:31,633 --> 00:12:32,733
Hello.

250
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:36,000
Did you really have
to say hello?

251
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:39,900
Can you please leave me alone?
Kiko, just go! [HUFFS]

252
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:42,567
I just said hello.
What's wrong with that?

253
00:12:42,567 --> 00:12:43,567
- Hi.
- Please, Kiko.

254
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:46,500
Isn't it obvious
I don't want to talk to you?

255
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:49,800
Is this still about the earring?

256
00:12:49,833 --> 00:12:51,900
Jade, I didn't know
it was yours.

257
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:53,967
[HUFFS]
Leave me alone, please!

258
00:12:53,967 --> 00:12:55,567
[SIGHS SHARPLY]

259
00:12:55,567 --> 00:12:57,200
Jade, we need
to talk about this.

260
